{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 13:06:10.106570", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary\\n- Overall health: Degraded. Two independent control-plane issues are preventing end-to-end connectivity for end hosts to the server farm.\\n- Primary anomalies detected:\\n  1) DHCP relay is not running on both distribution routers, so access hosts do not receive IP addresses.\\n  2) FRR/OSPF is down on router_core_3, isolating the server farm (10.200.0.0/24) from the rest of the network.\\n\\nFindings and Evidence\\n\\n1) Access hosts have no IP configuration (DHCP failure)\\n- host_1_1_1_1 and host_2_1_1_1 have eth0 up but no IPv4 configured; no routes:\\n  - host_1_1_1_1: ip addr shows only loopback; ip route is empty.\\n  - host_2_1_1_1: ip addr shows only loopback; ip route is empty.\\n- Pings from hosts fail immediately due to no IP:\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 -> dns_server/load_balancer: “Temporary failure in name resolution” (no DNS because no IP), and would be “Network is unreachable” for raw IPs.\\n- DHCP server is healthy/listening:\\n  - On dhcp_server, netstat shows UDP 0.0.0.0:67 served by dhcpd.\\n- DHCP relay is not running on both distribution routers:\\n  - router_dist_1_1: isc-dhcp-relay Active: inactive (dead)\\n  - router_dist_2_1: isc-dhcp-relay Active: inactive (dead)\\nImpact: End-hosts do not obtain addresses for their subnets (10.1.1.0/24, 10.2.1.0/24), cannot reach gateways, DNS, or any services.\\n\\n2) OSPF adjacency missing between the core and server farm (FRR down on core3)\\n- FRR on router_core_3 is not running:\\n  - router_core_3: frr.service Active: inactive (dead)\\n- server_access_router FRR is running but has no OSPF neighbors:\\n  - server_access_router: frr.service Active: active (running)\\n  - OSPF details show “Number of fully adjacent neighbors: 0” and “show ip ospf neighbor” lists none.\\n- As a result, server_access_router has only directly connected routes:\\n  - server_access_router routes: 10.200.0.0/24 via br0, 172.16.0.10/31 via eth7; no learned routes to 10.1.1.0/24 or 10.2.1.0/24.\\n- Distribution routers do not have a route to the server farm:\\n  - router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1 OSPF tables contain LANs and core P2P links (172.16.0.0/31, 0.2/31, 0.4/31, 0.6/31, 0.8/31), but no 172.16.0.10/31 (the link to server_access_router) and no 10.200.0.0/24.\\n- OSPF elsewhere is healthy:\\n  - router_core_1 and router_core_2 are fully adjacent with each other and their respective dist routers.\\nImpact: Even with proper host IPs, traffic from access networks would not reach 10.200.0.0/24 because the server farm is not advertised into the OSPF domain (loss of adjacency at core3).\\n\\n3) Server farm local connectivity is healthy\\n- Intra-server-farm reachability is normal (ICMP OK):\\n  - dhcp_server, dns_server, load_balancer, and web_server_[0-3] can ping each other with low RTTs.\\n- This confirms local switching/bridging on server_access_router and servers themselves are operating as expected.\\n\\nScope and Impact Assessment\\n- Client subnets 10.1.1.0/24 and 10.2.1.0/24: No DHCP, therefore no client IP addresses and no connectivity.\\n- Core/Distribution OSPF domain (core1/core2/dist routers): OSPF is stable within this subdomain.\\n- Server farm 10.200.0.0/24: Internally healthy, but isolated from the rest of the network because OSPF on core3 is down and server_access_router has no neighbors.\\n- End-to-end service access: Broken. Clients cannot even obtain IPs. Even with manual IP configuration, clients would still fail to reach 10.200.0.0/24 due to the OSPF isolation on router_core_3.\\n\\nRoot Cause(s)\\n- DHCP failure on access networks: isc-dhcp-relay service is inactive on both distribution routers (router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1).\\n- OSPF isolation of server farm: FRR is inactive on router_core_3, preventing OSPF adjacency with server_access_router and advertisement of 10.200.0.0/24 into the rest of the network.\\n\\nAffected Devices\\n- router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1: DHCP relay service not running.\\n- router_core_3: FRR/OSPF service not running.\\n\\nNo remediation steps are included here, per instructions., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='0ffd80a6-2d8d-451e-bdc7-9afd953f8640'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
